cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as novel view synthesis and 3D reconstruction, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to manipulating image content, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of spatial transformations and volumetric bottlenecks could also suggest a connection to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on image manipulation and reconstruction could also suggest a connection to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
